activityTypes.name: IC50
activityTypes.metadata: The half maximal inhibitory concentration (IC50) is a measure of the effectiveness of a substance in inhibiting a specific biological or biochemical function.

activityTypes.name: pIC50
activityTypes.metadata: This number assumes IC50 in nM unit, so it is calculated by 9 - log(IC50). Please change your data or the code to make it appropriate.
